      </div>

      <div class="apn-s-severity-display" id="apn-sleep-severity"></div>

      <h3 style="font-family:Georgia,serif; font-size:22px; color:#0D0D0D; margin:40px 0 8px;">Root Cause Identification</h3>
      <div class="apn-s-divider" style="width:40px; height:2px;"></div>
      <p class="apn-s-body">Based on your quiz score and your tier, your most likely root cause is one of three sub-gaps. Select the one that best describes your pattern.</p>

      <div class="apn-s-subgap-options" id="apn-sleep-subgaps">
        <button class="apn-s-subgap-btn" data-subgap="onset" onclick="apnSleepSelectSubgap(this)">
          Onset: I cannot fall asleep
          <span>Your mind races or your body feels alert when you lie down. Sleep onset takes 20 to 45 minutes or longer. Cortisol timing and blue light exposure are the most likely drivers.</span>
        </button>
        <button class="apn-s-subgap-btn" data-subgap="maintenance" onclick="apnSleepSelectSubgap(this)">
          Maintenance: I wake up mid-night
          <span>You fall asleep reasonably well but wake between 2am and 4am, often alert or anxious. This correlates with cortisol rebound and blood sugar fluctuation during the early morning hours.</span>
